history.content: 127 + 189 will almost certainly be harder, 161 + 162 may be more time consuming. Since these and theory versus programming classes the comparison is kind of apples and oranges. In my opinion 161 is probably the easiest upper div (not an easy class of course, but in comparison to other upper divs) and is normally a good thing to pair up with a harder CS upper div if you need to take 2 in one semester

gonna take 127+189 next sem, have taken 161+162 in a semester past (and planning to have a similar level of non-EECS-class work in both semesters) I know they might not be too comparable since I assume my upcoming schedule is more math-y but still wanted some input from people who took these classes/combos based on hours of work, general difficulty, etc. I'm going into 189 with no relevant experience other than 70/16B but planning to review a bit of lin alg over break.
history.subject: workload of 161+162 vs 127+189
